    <statement><p>Solve for <m>x</m> in the equation <m>mx^{2}+nx+p=0\text{,}</m> assuming <m>m\neq0\text{.}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{-n-\sqrt{n^{2}-4mp}}{2m}, \frac{-n+\sqrt{n^{2}-4mp}}{2m}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve a quadratic equation of the form <m>ax^{2}+bx+c=0\text{,}</m> we can use the quadratic formula. In this case, <m>a=m\text{,}</m> <m>b=n\text{,}</m> and <m>c=p\text{.}</m> Therefore the solutions are <m>\frac{-n+\sqrt{n^{2}-4mp}}{2m}, \frac{-n-\sqrt{n^{2}-4mp}}{2m}\text{,}</m> or <m>\frac{-n \pm \sqrt{n^{2}-4mp}}{2m}\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
